The simultaneous interpretation feature currently supports only human interpreters and does not support machine translation. Therefore, the feature can only be used with the assistance of professional interpreters.
At present, simultaneous interpretation can only be enabled when scheduling a meeting on the desktop client. This feature is not available for instant meetings or for scheduled meetings where simultaneous interpretation was not enabled during the scheduling process.
Enterprise Super Administrators and administrators with account setting permissions can configure the supported languages for the simultaneous interpretation feature via the Admin Console: Account Management > Account Settings > Meeting Settings. By default, the feature supports 17 languages: Chinese, English, Japanese, Korean, German, French, Russian, Portuguese, Spanish, Italian, Arabic, Indonesian, Hindi, Thai, Vietnamese, Malay, and Turkish.
